Yellow card policy
System of 3 warnings.

1st warning
-Occurs when a task has not been completed during a sprint, and the responsible person has no reasonable explanation.
    -It is recorded in the team log for further reference.

2nd warning
-Occurs after a second offence with no reasonable explanation
    -Team intervention. Why is the person not completing the tasks given/chosen and work sa a team to form a solution to help the offender improve their workload. Noted to the PO as well, with possible solutions.

3rd Warning
-Occurs after repeated offending, and the offender hasn't changed their ways even after intervention. 
     -Escalated directly to teaching staff.

